After rooting around online even more, it seemed issue [https://github.com/ARMmbed/mbed-os/issues/4532](https://github.com/ARMmbed/mbed-os/issues/4532) captured a description of my problem.

But it seems like a lot of these similar problems were recently solved by pr [https://github.com/ARMmbed/mbed-os/pull/4543](https://github.com/ARMmbed/mbed-os/pull/4543)

I also found this post from over a year ago that seems very similar, the fact that no solution was found makes me feel like my current hardware design is dead in the water:
[https://developer.mbed.org/questions/61589/Program-hangs-at-SetSysClock-on-a-custom/](https://developer.mbed.org/questions/61589/Program-hangs-at-SetSysClock-on-a-custom)

Any ideas of what I should do? I felt like this must have been a hardware issue when I first started. But now I see that I can run & debug code if I use the system default clock, so I should be able to configure the HSI to run at a reasonabe speed, preferably with the Mbed environment!

